description.en-US: Wavetrain offers a unique train detection solution for level/grade crossings. Sensors placed on the train tracks detects the acoustic sounds of approaching trains. Advanced software distinguishes trains from other sound sources for safe train detection. The Wavetrain’s solution stands out as a new and innovative offer in a huge market with a need to increase safety for pedestrians and motorist crossing railways.

Light Structures provides fibre-optic technology that monitors surfaces prone to wear and tear. The firm is currently the global leader in hull monitoring. It is mainly focused on maritime vessels and construction, such as shipping, military, and offshore vessels, as well as wind turbines.

Hybrid Energy provides industrial heat pumps with highly efficient energy recovery rates. A regular ammonia-only pump can heat water up to 50°C. In comparison, Hybrid Energy can use the same equipment to heat water to 120°C. It uses a mixture of water and ammonia which works as a natural refrigerant. In addition, between 15-65°C of wasted heat can be recovered.

Clarity offers solutions to efficiently clear water. Through its patented technology, the firm allows for efficient CO2 removal using the downdraft principle and aerification methods to maintain the oxygen concentration in the water. Additionally, Clarity provides protein skimming solutions to remove organic waste in water. These applications can be used in both fresh and saltwater and are friendly to the environment CLARITY WTS AS offers a unique and patented technology to reduce unwanted organic waste from fresh and saltwater in an efficient and environmentally friendly manner. In addition, the downdraft principle and aerification allow for an efficient CO2 degassing. The protein skimmer is available in several sizes, ranging from small applications to sizes suitable for larger land-based recirculation systems.

Nicarnica provides detection solutions software. The company currently has two product lines; a volcanic ash detection system (AVOID) and an object detection system (NEVADAS). AVOID can detect volcanic ash. This solution can be stationed on a plane and on the ground. Using infrared and ultraviolet sensing technology, an airborne solution can detect ash from a distance of 100km. NEVADAS can detect objects in any kind of weather up to 250m. By using infrared imagery and machine vision, the software can recognize and categorize object.

Franatech is the sole actor providing subsea sensors at extreme depths with the only point sensor technology available. Its products have been qualified by Equinor (formerly Statoil) to last up to 25 years 4000 meters below sea level, with little-to-no maintenance. Franatech provides the only sensors in the world that can detect oil and gas leaks at extreme depths with minimal maintenance.

Genetic Analysis (GA) is a world leader within molecular diagnostics, specialized in the field of mapping microbiota. The company develops In Vitro Diagnostics (IVD) using its own mapping technology that can detect all diseases involving microbiota.

Solid Publication AS is a SaaS (Software as a Service) company that develops and market web-based tools which enable the customer to easily and professionally manage and analyze company activities across multiple channels in social media. Solid Publication is helping companies and people manage the complexity of this new social paradigm by producing tools and solutions which are more simple, affordable and effective than any other social media systems available in the market.
Seacalx provides a natural biocide product to combat lice in salmon and trout farms. The bicoide is safe for both the fish and its consumers and does not harm the environment.

One2Touch provides covers for smartphones using Near Field Communication (NFC). The company wants to apply this technology for continuous communication on Machine-to-Machine and IoT platforms, as well as the embedded hardware/software to allow these devices to interact. Additionally, One2Touch is the first company in the world to offer wireless keyboards for smartphones. These “smart” covers have keyboards and/or display attached to them and can be used for work, gaming and more.

METAS provides subsea sonar and camera solutions. The technologies can be utilized for detection oil and gas leaks, and for monitoring maritime ecosystems. METAS currently provides 11 product lines, including batteries, cameras, sub-sea connectors, software and more.

Icefresh is a high-end salmon supplier mainly focused on the Chinese market. The company possesses a patented freezing technology that ensures the fish is as fresh upon delivery as when it was caught.  The freezing technology allows delivery of fresh fish JIT from a local warehouse. Defrosting the fish to a fresh state only takes an hour.

Hammertech offers a low-cost water detector solution that can be integrated into components in oil production. The detector is able to monitor the flow of oil product in real-time and identifies wells that pump up excess water. Hammertech’s detector is robust, proven and does not interfere with production.

BerGenBio AS is a biotech company built on proprietary Screening technology used for the research and pre-clinical development of novel drug targets, associated biomarkers and first in class therapeutics for the treatment of cancer, with lead programs against metastatic drug resistant solid tumors, EMT and drug resistance. BerGenBio’s is driven by a powerful technology platform called CellSelect that provides greater biological insight to the role and function of targets and illustrates therapeutic benefit through regulated dose response therapeutically mimetic studies of target inhibition and translational preclinical modeling.

Stingray offers a patented optical laser delousing device service to the fish farming industry with a state of the art technical platform supported by software applications. By using stereo camera vision, advanced software and targeted laser, lice removal is fully automated around the clock, seven days a week throughout the year, without any handling of the fish. The stereo camera and proprietary software detects lice as the salmon swims in the pen. A guided laser pulse of up to 150 milliseconds "pulses" directly at each individual louse.

CrayoNano can grow nanowires on graphene used in UV LED and is the first in the world to do so. These nanowires allow for large UV light emissions from a small surface, increasing the efficiency 10 times while reducing the costs by 10% to that of existing mercury-based UV lamps. In addition, CrayoNano offers a more reliability and operating lifetime compared to old solutions.

Hystorsys provides hydrogen compressors. The compressors use metal hydride alloys to absorb and release hydrogen simply by cooling and heating them, respectively. The metal alloys also remove impurities and maintains high H2 purity. This system is customizable and highly efficient, especially with access to waste heat or geothermal heat.

Initial Force provides software that can record and analyse athletic motion, marketed under the Swing Catalyst brand. The products are integrated and allow athletes and instructors to optimise performance through advanced analysis.

Ceramic Powder is a supplier of composites and powders. The company has currently 139 products in its portfolio, using 40 elements. These materials have mainly three areas of use: in solid oxide fuel cells, in gas separation membranes and lead-free electroceramics. The company also offers tailor-made composites and powders.

The company is developing cost leading insulation and buoyancy material for deep water applications such as floating buoys and risers targeted for water depths between 1,000 - 5,000 meters. The material has low density and can endure high pressure for underwater use.

CondAlign provides a technological solution to align electrically conductive material to restructure the material into film or composite. The process allows retains material characteristics and reduces the need for fillers which reduces costs. The patented technology is well suited for roll-to-roll, a high-speed manufacturing process.

Augmenti provides real-time decision support system and situational awareness solutions for military use. The software allows one to see “virtual” objects/signs blended into the user’s “real” vision. This allows one to become informed of one’s surroundings visually that one cannot see with the naked eye.

Bitreactive provides software focused on the Internet of things (IoT) and software development. The company helps with connecting devices to the internet, select hardware for data collection and manage data flow. Its solutions can be applied in homes and on an industrial scale. Bitreacitve’s BALT product line is a personal hub that connects rooms, collects data, organises that data through a gateway and distributed relevant information.

Boostcom develops and provides mobile marketing and mobile advertising loyalty programmes and integrated advertising solutions based on data-driven customer insight to help owners of large customer databases to increase sales.

APT is a provider of high-quality laboratory analyses and services to the oil & gas industry within the fields of petroleum geochemistry, biostratigraphy, sedimentology, structural geology, and basin modeling, including multi-client (MC) studies.

APIM provides anti-cancer drugs based on a discovery by a professor at a leading research university in Norway (NTNU). The company has currently five drugs in the pipeline and human trials for one of these drugs will be conducted this year. The firm also has a fully-owned subsidiary in Australia to conduct trials there and to benefit from its generous R&D tax incentives.

Polarworks has developed and patented the next-generation 3D motion control technology, with applications in consumer and enterprise markets, automation and robotics. Two main areas of technology development; ALTA, a fully operating 3D consumer printer and PolarDrive, software application enabling the motion control.

RPT provides software that interprets seismic data and predicts porosity, lithology and fluid saturation. This software is particularly useful in the exploration, appraisal and production of hydrocarbons in the Oil & Gas industry.

Mazemap provides mapping and navigation solutions for use in large buildings. Such buildings include universities, malls, hospitals, venues/exhibitions and more. The platform offers features such as indoor mapping, navigation & positioning, data collection, and content management, integration with other devices (IoT) and applied programming interface (API) for mobile applications.

Inhibio provides additives that prevent the formation of bacterial biofilm. Biofilm, the formation of the bacterial community that increases their chances of survival, causes billions of dollars’ worth of damage every year. There has been an increase in regulations against biocides to combat biofilm due to its toxicity.

Holberg EEG provides software for the monitoring and reporting on electrical activity in the brain. Ph.D. Harald Aurlien MD, one of the co-founders of Holberg, developed the standard method of interpreting EEG data and is now being developed into a global standard.

Glucoset offers monitoring devices to measure blood glucose levels. Current solutions are either inaccurate or time-consuming and infrequent. As a result, mortality among patients with high glucose levels for patients in intensive care units is high. Glucoset has developed a sensor that can be integrated with arterial catheters used today.

Televenture Management aims to provide its investors with precise and relevant information at all times. We want to have an open and direct dialogue with our shareholders and other stakeholders. Televenture Management will hold several presentations throughout each calendar year and will on occasions invite portfolio companies to provide a more in-depth presentation of their business.

selfDescription.en-US: Mr. Rinnan founded Televenture in 1993 and has top-level international and financial experience in telecom, IT, media and the Oil & Gas sector. From 1993 until 2010, Mr. Rinnan was the CEO and Managing Partner of several Telenor Venture funds. Prior to this, Mr. Rinnan was senior vice president and CFO of ABB Oil & Gas and ABB Signal. He holds a Master of Science in Business and Economics (siviløkonom), with a major in Finance from the Norwegian School of Management.

Mr. Slåttsveen joined Televenture in 2010 with a long international senior management background within the Oil & Gas and Process industries. Before joining Televenture Capital he was CFO of Wega Mining ASA and SVP/CFO of Aker Solution’s global subsea group located in Houston, USA. Mr. Slåttsveen holds a BS and a MBA in Finance and Management from California State University, Hayward, USA.

Mr. Sørum joined Televenture in 1998. Prior to joining Televenture, Mr. Sørum was a private investor and a senior adviser for European companies working in both Asia and the Middle East. Mr. Sørum has held several board positions in Norwegian investment companies. Mr. Sørum holds a Master of Science in Business and Economics (siviløkonom) from Copenhagen School of Economics and Business Administration. Mr. Sørum is a Norwegian citizen with residence in Oslo, Norway.

Mr. Nilsen joined Televenture in 2009. He was previously Investment Director at Kjeller Innovasjon AS and Technology Advisor for the Norwegian Trade Council in San Francisco. He has also been an affiliated researcher at the Stanford Research Institute Learning on Demand Program in California. Mr. Nilsen has master studies in Political Science and International Economics at the University of Oslo and holds a BA in ComputerScience and Cognitive Science from the same university. Mr. Nilsen is a Norwegian citizen with residence in Oslo, Norway.

Mr. Rian joined Televenture Management in 2009. He was the founder of  SPT Group (former Scandpower Petroleum Technology) that was first sold to Altor Private Equity Partners in 2006 and later to Schlumberger Inc in 2012. He has extensive international experience and key competence within business development including marketing, sale, and organizational development, in addition to mergers and acquisitions. Mr. Rian holds a MSc. in Petroleum Technology from The Norwegian Institute of Technology in Trondheim (1982). Mr. Rian is a Norwegian citizen with residence in Oslo, Norway.

Mrs. Pettersen joined Televenture in 2013 having worked for Scandinavian Airlines Systems (SAS) from 1990 until 2013. During this period she held various positions as cabin crew and the last 4 years as Air Purser (Chief in Cabin). In addition, Mrs. Pettersen worked in the SAS administration focusing on products and procedures. From 2008 to 2012 she recruited new cabin crew for SAS. She holds a Bachelor of Arts degree from the University of Oslo and is a Norwegian citizen with residence in Oslo, Norway.
